### Statement Parser Dispatch (`parse_stmt()` - parser.h:521-720)

The statement parser uses **if-else chains** to dispatch on current token type:

```
parse_stmt():
├── IF (TOK_IF) → parse IF/THEN/ELSE
│   ├── Parse condition
│   ├── Parse THEN branch (either DO...END block or single statement)
│   └── Optional ELSE branch
│
├── DO (TOK_DO) variants:
│   ├── DO WHILE (condition) → parse counted loop
│   ├── DO I = start TO end → parse loop control
│   └── DO; ... END; → parse simple block
│
├── CALL (TOK_CALL) → parse procedure call statement
│   ├── Get procedure name
│   └── Optional parameter list in parens
│
├── RETURN (TOK_RETURN) → parse return statement
│   └── Optional expression in parens
│
├── DCL/DECLARE → delegate to parse_dcl()
│
└── Default: parse_primary() + postfix operators
    ├── If followed by TOK_EQ → parse assignment (nd_left = lvalue, nd_right = rvalue)
    └── Else → expression statement (bare function call or array element)
```

**KEY FINDING**: There is **NO case for TOK_ASM** in `parse_stmt()` - this needs to be added!

---

### PROC Parsing (`parse_proc()` - parser.h:826-939)

PROC nodes have this structure:
```c
nd_name[n]  = procedure name
nd_left[n]  = first parameter (PARAM nodes linked via nd_next)
nd_right[n] = body (BLOCK node)
nd_ival[n]  = option flags (bit flags):
    bit 0: OPT_FREESTANDING
    bit 1: OPT_NAKED
    bit 2: OPT_LEAF
nd_stor[n]  = return type (TYPE_ constant, TYPE_NONE if no RETURNS)
```

**OPTIONS parsing** (parser.h:878-900):
```c
if (cur_type == TOK_OPTIONS) {
    parse_advance();
    parse_expect(TOK_LPAREN);
    while (cur_type != TOK_RPAREN && !parse_err) {
        if (cur_type == TOK_FREESTANDING) {
            opts = opts | OPT_FREESTANDING;
        } else if (cur_type == TOK_NAKED) {
            opts = opts | OPT_NAKED;
        } else if (cur_type == TOK_LEAF) {
            opts = opts | OPT_LEAF;
        }
        parse_advance();
        if (cur_type == TOK_COMMA) parse_advance();
    }
    parse_expect(TOK_RPAREN);
}
```

